
[1]congregational

   CONGREGATIONAL, a. Pertaining to a congregation; appropriately used of
   such Christians as hold to church government by consent and election,
   maintaining that each congregation is independent of others, and has
   the right to choose its own pastor and govern itself; as a
   congregational church, or mode of worship.
